10 compensate an employee or a teacher prior to retirement for each
11 unused sick leave day the teacher or employee has accrued in excess
12 of fifteen (15) days, provided the employee or teacher has elected to
13 receive compensation for the excess unused sick leave. The rate of
14 compensation for each unused sick leave day shall be based on a
15 percentage of the daily salary rate calculated from the employee's or
16 teacher's last annual salary, not to exceed thirty percent (30%). The
17 school district may establish additional requirements for payment of
18 unused sick leave days established under this paragraph, including
